@node OGFX "Object/Aliens BMP graphics"
 @{b}@{u}BitMap Graphics for Objects/Aliens.@{uu}@{ub}

 This is a Wee-bit complicated, but let's give it a shot:


 @{u}Drawing Graphics@{uu}

 Graphics should be drawn in a Bitmap drawing program like DPAINT or  PPaint,
 the  graphics MUST be drawn on a lowres screen using 32 colours. If you like
 to be a little smart (and kind to yourselve), then you should define a  size
 of  each  frame  you wish to draw (note the size down) and use this size for
 each and every frame. And then fill the maximum of frames across the screen,
 so  if your drawing on a 320 pix. wide screen and has each frame 32 pix wide
 then you put 10 frames in each row. This opens up  for  the  possibility  of
 automatic calculating the frames later on. If you're drawing aliens then you
 need to draw frames for at least 4 side-views  (front,  back,  left,  right)
 however  the  left/right  can be combined as the game is capable of flipping
 frames..


 @{u}Converting the graphics@{uu}

 Ok, now you have drawn your graphics as descriped before. Then you  need  to
 convert  the picture into the format used by the game. Enter the 'Set Object
 GFX Frames' and select 'Conv. BMP Frames'. You'll now be asked to select the
 IFF  file,  and then to enter some information about the file (framesize and
 number of frames). Then sit back and wait a while for the  converter  to  do
 it's job..

 Now there's only left to put the converted file into the system and  setting
 up the various frames..

 @{" Click Here to read about that " link M0201}

@endnode

