@node WGFX "Converting Wall-graphics"

 Wallgraphics was  originaly  converted  with  the  '256wall'  program,  I've
 included it in the main editor and rewritten it a little bit, so here's some
 new instructions:

 Drawing graphics:
 -----------------
 Graphics are drawn in a normal drawingprogram, and must be saved as IFF, you
 can  use  2->32  colours  in  the  drawing  process,  but  remember that the
 converter changes the colours to match with the internal palette used by the
 game,  so  the  colours  might  not  be excatly the same as the one's you've
 choosen, the converter makes a match to try and  find  a  colour  that's  as
 close  as  posible,  but  some  times it misses a bit.. Several tiles can be
 drawn next to eachother, but don't make the screen width more that 640,  the
 game  can't handle it. Each tile should have a width of 16,32,64,128 or 256,
 if you use other sizes you'll get in trouble when including them, the height
 of  the  tiles  is  less sensitive, but should be at least 8, to make things
 more easy you should try to hold the values at 8,16,32,64,128,256 or 512, if
 you  choose  to  use  other  heights make sure the height is even, or you'll
 proberly have something looking quite odd..

 Converting:
 -----------
 The converter can be found in the 'Define walls'  section,  simply  hit  the
 function, and choose your IFF-file, unlike the 'old' converter this will try
 to figure out the width and height of the file, these will  be  the  default
 values,  so  when  the  converter  asks for 'width' and 'height' the numbers
 shown are the defaults and will be  activated  if  you  just  press  'enter'
 without any number.. The converter will start out by getting the palette and
 then getting the drawed data, if you think that  the  palette-generation  is
 taking  longer  than before, you're proberly rigt, I've tried to enhance the
 selection of colours to make it hit better, and it takes a  little  longer..
 When  saving  the  file simply enter the name you'd like, the converter will
 add '.256wad' if you don't..

 Notes:
 ------
 - If you're changing a wall defined in the list (converting again  with  the
   same name) and you have changed the height of the chunck you MUST reselect
   the file, if you don't the graphics will screw up..

@endnode

